# To-Do List Application (Console-Based)

##  Overview
This is a simple command-line To-Do List app built in Python.  
It supports adding, removing, and viewing tasks, and stores them in a text file (`tasks.txt`) for persistence.

##  Features
- Add new tasks
- View all tasks
- Remove tasks by number
- Tasks remain saved even after closing the app
- Uses Python file handling (open, read, write)
- Uses lists for storage

##  Files Included
- `todo.py` → Main application script
- `tasks.txt` → Stores your tasks (auto-created)

